## §2. Π_survival ENGINE DESIGN

### §2.1 Signal inputs (4 signals)

| signal | source | exists | unit |
|---|---|---|---|
| `rate_pressure` | event arrival rate / capacity | ✅ BackPressureGuard.health() in `src/core/guards/eventbus.guard.ts` | [0, 1] |
| `queue_depth` | queue.length / threshold | ✅ QuantumBuffer.getQueueLength() in `src/core/quantum/quantum-buffer.engine.ts` | [0, 1] |
| `recovery_potential` | regression from failure cases | ❌ NEEDS_DATA (qiint2 #6) | [0, 1] |
| `time_radiation` | accumulated stress over time | ✅ SPEC_RADIATION_UNIVERSAL Section B | [0, ∞) |

### §2.2 Formula draft (geometric mean — penalize worst signal)

```
Π_survival(cell, t) = (
  (1 - rate_pressure_normalized) ×
  (1 - queue_depth_normalized) ×
  recovery_potential ×
  exp(-time_radiation_accumulation × γ_survival)
)^(1/4)

where:
  γ_survival = ln(2) / τ_overdrive
  τ_overdrive = 300s (per SPEC_QIINT_PHYSICS §6 overdrive-recoverable)
```

**Lý do geometric mean (KHONG arithmetic):**
- Arithmetic mean: 1 signal yeu co the bi mask boi 3 signal khoe
- Geometric mean: 1 signal -> 0 keo Π_survival -> 0 → **catch failure som** (butterfly effect ve 1)

### §2.3 Thresholds (NEEDS_CALIBRATION)

```
🚨 ALL THRESHOLDS BELOW = GUESSED, NEEDS_DATA TO CALIBRATE 🚨

Π_survival > 0.90  → ACCEPT (healthy, full traffic)
0.85 ≤ Π_survival ≤ 0.90 → BACKPRESSURE (warn upstream slow down)
0.80 ≤ Π_survival < 0.85 → LOAD_SHED (drop priority < threshold)
Π_survival < 0.80 → CIRCUIT_BREAK (refuse all, half-open after τ_recovery)
```

**Calibration plan (per bang_pending_20260420 P1.5):**
- Stress test: ramp rate_pressure 0 → 2.0 × capacity, log when cell fails
- Use 90th percentile of failure points as threshold floor
- Adjust safety margin = -2σ from observed failures

