## §4. INTEGRATION POINTS

### §4.1 Wire Π_survival into existing lifecycle

Per SPEC_QIINT_PHYSICS §6:

| lifecycle | requires Π_survival check |
|---|---|
| `clone` | Π_body > 0.85 (no Π_survival check yet — shall add?) |
| `overdrive-recoverable` | **`Π_survival > 0.9`** ← already in spec |
| `resurrect` | (no Π_survival check — shall add for resurrected cells?) |

→ Engine emit `Π_survival` qua EventBus → lifecycle decisions consume.

### §4.2 EventBus contract

```
Event: SURVIVAL_METRIC_UPDATE
Payload: {
  cell_id: string,
  Π_survival: number,
  signals: SurvivalSignals,
  decision: SurvivalDecision,
  timestamp: ISO8601,
}
Frequency: every 100ms or on signal change > 5%
```

